# Frontend Next.js stack

## Baseline

- App Router: routes live under `frontend/app/` (not `src/` until you migrate).
- Scripts: `npm run dev` (`next dev`), `npm run build`, `npm run start`, `npm run lint` (`eslint`).
- Stack: Next 16.x, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind v4 (`tailwindcss`, `@tailwindcss/postcss`), ESLint (`eslint`, `eslint-config-next`).
- Config: `next.config.ts`, `eslint.config.mjs`.

## Do not

- Replace Next scripts with Vite or add `react-router`; App Router owns routing.
- Put browser-only APIs or client-only libraries in Server Components without checking docs.

## Do

- Use `"use client"` only where hooks, events, or browser APIs require it.
- Expose browser env vars only as `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
- Prefer `npm run lint` and `npm run build` before merge.

## Optional tooling (not in baseline)

- Prettier, Husky, lint-staged, Jest/Vitest—add in phased PRs; do not assume they exist in `package.json`.
